				I would like to put in my 2 copper worth on the Mage/wizzie thing since it seems to be the thing most are interested in. I have a lvl 49 wizard and a lvl 52 paladin and I find both of my characters to be totally awesome in some respects adn totally depressing in other respects. My paladin used to be an Awesome tank, then he hit 50 and now its a whole different world for him. I look at other tank classes with envy at times cause im not giving out the most dmg. That seems to be the time I play my wizard, now I can definately deal out the most damage, but the fun lvl goes down a bit seeing how I really love to be beat on alot and actually live through it. I think on the subject of mage/wiz duel it would be alot easier for a mage to win in general, but I would love watching the few Wizards that are smart enough to actually use there brain and beat the mage. I have done this duel an a few occasions with a few mage friends and I have won several times but I have lost more often. I like to think im very good at dueling also. as far as class envy goes my wiz has absolutely no class envy on a mage, im a dungeon fighter at heart and I know my class well. Wizards are meant to be group fighters and Mage is definately more solo class (not that I cant solo as good as any mage since getting 44) My real class envy comes from my Paladin against mages.  can you imagine having 50+kpp in equipment and watching a mage come in and summon a pet for what 2-4pp? and watching that pet not only out damage you, but COMPLETELY blow away almost 2 tanks of your lvl in any one fight dmg wise, and lets not forget the 1k dmg they put out with spells while thier pet casually does what a 53 warrior in a berserker frenzie whiile using a discipline cant even match. You guys can bet My wizzie is Awesome and there is no need to compare him to a mage, its my mele class that really have issues with OVER blown classes like mage/necro  there is much room to Nerf here I think.
