	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Relikk, thanks for the best post on this page yet.  I'm not a wizard, I'm just a curious enchanter.  I'm not here to talk about duels, even though I'm on Tallon Zek.  Just wanted to add a few probably unsaid things about grouping/classes in general.  Usually, when I group for exp, I don't have a wizard in my group (although I do give the ones that ask for it clarity most of the time).  However, I usually group on the plains, which I guess is weird for enchanters, as the class is best suited to dungeons.  The big catch here is that inside of a dungeon, if there was a choice between going with a mage or a wizard, I'd choose the wizard every time unless we were farming the thing, and the wizard was at least 10 levels above every mob in the place.  Mages never seem to work out with mezmerize because they can't seem to get their pets off when they choose the wrong targets, and I haven't seen many with enough brains to assist the puller (if we're in a group of more than 2 people, anyways) before telling their pet to attack, and nuke the same target.  That or they use aoe's or some hairball thing like that which breaks mezzes anyways.  I'm not trying to say mages suck.  They're great when they're played right, and they're almost always great on the plains, where you're usually facing one enemy at a time.  Wizards have their downside in groups outside of dungeons.  They can't deal as much damage as a mage in the same amount of time because the mage has a pet.  The biggest thing I've observed is that the wizard class tends to be more of a thinking class than the mage class.  Whereas mages can usually and almost always try to use sheer force, the wizard can accomplish most of the same goals, but has to use more brains.  They spend more of their time medding, and only get a good way to increase mana at level 34 or so.  It's a tough class to play.  I have respect for wizards for the same reason, and whenever there ARE wizards that want to group where I am, if there's no list, they're in.  Especially in dungeons.  When you start saying that your class is better than the other classes, in a way, you're really saying you need a  handicap in the game, if your classes power comes in the form of something solid like nukes that deal more than the premier nuking classes nukes, or pets that can solo melee classes of the same level.  Even melee classes have to think more than mages because they're almost always in groups after level 20 or so.  If you think that mages and necros are more powerful than wizards, then in turn you imply that wizards (because there ARE high level wizards out there)  are probably better players (assuming they do get up there, I'm not trying to say that just because you're playing a wizard you're awesome) than mages or necros.  This is a game of intelligence.  If you can win the game with less power, then you're probably smarter than those that can't.  In my opinion, the point that you're bragging that you can beat wizards all the time just proves that you have a big ego.  Even with the play by play crap, there was one wizard that used strategy, and broke the mage.  Also, I hardly ever ask for magicians to summon weapons/other stuff for me.  I get teleports once about every 2 or 3 days.  I'd have to say that without wizards, I wouldn't even play this game due to the amount of time I'd spend just wandering from place to place.  Everyone who was talking about play balance is right.  If any mage acted like all these &quot;mages are gods&quot; posters in the game, they probably wouldn't get a port anywhere except by druids.. good luck on the plains, moron.  Any class that has too much sheer power, like mages and necros, usually ends up sucking at grouping, and in turn gets a little less out of the game.  If you're one of the idiots posting about how great you are at dueling on this board, why not go play a game where there aren't other people involved, like Pong.  You obviously aren't good at working with other people anyways.  That's what separates this game from most other games, in my opinion.  Quake, etc.. is good too, but to be honest, I got board of it, and I wasn't a Quake God.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
