	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				For Pestilinces, and all the other level 1-40s who say how great your class is compared<BR>
to wizards, you obviously don't understand the way wizards are designed.  For starters,<BR>
wizards DO have a very hard time until level 44.  So if you duel a wizard at level 30,<BR>
and think this applies to those who are able to cast rend/Ice Comet, you obviously<BR>
don't know much about what a level 44 and up wizard is able to do.  <BR>
<BR>
Wizards starting at 20 can:<BR>
Interupt casting with a solid amount of DD damage<BR>
stun with a low amount of DD damage<BR>
Root<BR>
AoE snare<BR>
shadow step line of spells.<BR>
<BR>
Now, think about what would happen.  Any wizard would just avoid the pet.  It's not<BR>
too difficult, and once the mage or necro is gone, the pet no longer matters.  <BR>
With Stun effects, the other won't be able to cast, which gives a lot of time<BR>
to the wizard to cast another DD spell.  Also, in a duel situation, a wizard will<BR>
NEVER try to use Ice Comet.  When fighting another caster, interupt and stun<BR>
is the ONLY spells a wizard will need.  The casting time is fairly low as well, but<BR>
wizards change dramatically from 43 to 44.  The damage output goes WAY<BR>
up, from 400 to 600 damage for relatively little mana increase.<BR>
<BR>
For those who think that wizards 51+ could be beaten, the new spells have a VERY <BR>
VERY VERY low casting time.  Think you can survive against a DD that has only a<BR>
3 second casting time?  Don't think that because you can beat a wizard easily<BR>
at the lower levels means it will always be easy.  There is also a major mana <BR>
increase for each level over 50, so a level 51 wizard can do amazing damage<BR>
compared to a level 49.<BR>
<BR>
On the subject of Rend, it is a Direct Damage(DD) Spell.  It does a good amount<BR>
of damage, and doesn't need to be researched(you can BUY this spell).  Because<BR>
it does less damage than Ice Comet, it will also taunt less.  For all you<BR>
non-wizards that read this, why do you even post comparisons about your<BR>
class vs. the wizard class anyway?  If you don't play a wizard, stick to your own<BR>
class spell lists for posting.  Blow your own horn somewhere else.  And if you <BR>
havn't hit level 40 yet, you havn't earned the right to even compare your<BR>
class to another when talking about life at 49+.<BR>
<BR>
Targonis Manastorm<BR>
Level 47 Wizard<BR>
Ebony Order Guild<BR>
The Nameless
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
