				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay, I just went through seven pages of listening to people rant and ramble on about who can beat who. I have played all classes and anyone can beat anyone. I like my wizard most of all though, warriors just hit auto attack, and click a button or two. Same for all melee classes. Bards are great for groups, but not very good solo, niether is a wizard, thats the whole point. A wizard could beat a mage or necro most of the time. I've done it myself, it just depends on how you play. Hit yonder or shadow step first thing and then play with them from afar. But a mage and necro can solo, and thier pets are good in groups for absorbing some damage so that our tanks can last longer and get in extra damage before the mobs aggro on them. Balance. I believe that wizards should have less mana cost for most spells, especially in lower levels since you can only cast a few times before medding, but that plays into balance also. I don't think I have seen one post about the spell since coming to this page. Will someone please post some relevant info on this spell and try to stop the bickering, if you want to find out who would beat who duel yourself and leave the speculation to your own minds. And don't post anymore about who can beat who. Anybody can beat anybody, it all comes down to the skill of the player. Thank you for your time.
