				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hi all,<BR>
<BR>
Boy this is a long thread isn't it?  I'd just like<BR>
to point out a few things that naysayers in here who've<BR>
been attacking all other classes and announcing their <BR>
domininance among players have failed to mention.  First <BR>
and foremost, when you get right down to it, Everquest<BR>
is a &quot;video game&quot;.  Say it with me, &quot;video game&quot;.  Albeit an<BR>
interactive one with multiple users, the basics of playing <BR>
it go right back to your old Mario Brothers games and what not.  <BR>
I say this because playing EQ along with any other video game takes<BR>
SKILL.  When you played Mario Brothers a long time ago did you actually<BR>
get to Bowser and beat him on your first try? I know I didn't.  It took<BR>
a long time to develop the skills to play the game well and win it.<BR>
The same applies for EQ, you can't just sit down and expect to be the best<BR>
at what you do immediately. Like it or not, some people aren't good at video or <BR>
computer games.  This entire statement applies to my belief that no one class is <BR>
the best, rather it depends on the person behind the keyboard to win a duel, etc.<BR>
A few other people in this thread have recognized this fact, and I salute them.  <BR>
If we were to recognize that every person sitting behind the keyboard were different,<BR>
maybe we would realize that every character we duel will present a different challenge,<BR>
despite class and race restrictions.  Anyway, thanks for taking the time to read my <BR>
2 cp :P<BR>
<BR>
Erikkin <BR>
34th Wiz of the Rathe
